The construction of configure script seems to rely on very new
version of the GNU autotools, so I ended up running them on fnalu (fsui03):

aclocal -I m4
autoheader
automake
autoconf
./configure --with-cfitsio=/das2/data/src/cfitsio --datadir=/das2/data/imaging
make dist

This procedure creates the distribution file (eg sdssdrc-1.0.tar.gz) that
can be built on other machines (even those with old autotools):

$ cd sdssdrc-1.0
$ ./configure \
> --with-cfitsio-includedir=/opt/cfitsio/include  \
> --with-cfitsio-libdir=/opt/cfitsio/lib  \
> --datadir=/srv/das/imaging
$ make
$ cp drC /srv/das/www/cgi-bin

